// No external codec dependency: this is the decompressor everything downstream
// (gzip HTTP bodies, PNG IDAT, git objects) needs. Structure follows Mark Adler's
// puff.c — canonical-Huffman decode via count/symbol tables, LSB-first bit reader —
// but reworked to Milo ownership: state is a struct, input is a borrowed &string,
// output accumulates in an owned string (bytes, like std/base64).
//
// Internal helpers return an i64 status (0 ok, negative = error code) instead of
// threading Result through the hot path; the public entry points map that to Result.

