// ── FdReader: green-aware byte reads ──

// A read cursor over a raw fd whose read strategy is fixed at construction:
// under the green scheduler it parks the task on the event loop at EAGAIN; on a
// plain OS thread it blocks in the kernel. attach() decides once from runtime
// truth and welds that choice to the fd's O_NONBLOCK state, so no caller ever
// threads an "in green?" flag — the sharp edge where a wrong bool either stalls
// the whole cooperative runtime (a blocking read inside a green task) or spins
